Actually, I care.  I care about the fact I have spent three years and hundreds of hours on a toon.  I care that when all is said and done that the time I have spent on improving my Warrior's has less impact than a spell a knight gets at level 15 or 22 or whenever.  I care about the fact that I have struggled with the second worse class DPS in game.  I care that Warriors gave up almost all versatility so they could excell in the one thing they do and are supposed to do well.  I care that it as pretty much been made irrelevant by one expansion where it is so important to slow ASAP and that once the mob is slowed almost anyone can tank that Warriors are pretty much an after thought these days.<br>
<br>
As a class we made sacrafices and gave up functionality with the promise that we would be the best in one way.  That bargain hasn't really been upheld.  And now, we're having to beg to even be allowed to be on par with the other tank classes.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, but I care. <p>The Man in Black: We are men of action, lies do not become us. <br>
